Berjaya, MSM Malaysia, MISC, Teck Guan: Malaysia Stock Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-06-27T23:57:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/berjaya-msm-malaysia-misc-teck-guan-malaysia-stock-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Malaysia  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index fell 0.1 percent to
1,562.52.        Berjaya Land Bhd. (BL)  : The Malaysian property and
gaming group had a net loss of 4.69 million ringgit ($1.5
million) in the fourth quarter ended April 30, compared with a
profit of 72.1 million ringgit a year earlier, it said in a
statement. The stock was unchanged at 1.06 ringgit.  MSM Malaysia Holdings Bhd. (MSM MK): Shares of Malaysia’s
biggest sugar refiner will make its debut on the Kuala Lumpur
stock exchange. The company sold shares to institutional
investors at 3.50 ringgit each and to individual investors at
3.38 ringgit apiece in its initial public offering.  MISC Bhd. (MISC)  : Moody’s Investors Service placed the
Malaysian shipping group’s rating on review for a possible
downgrade to reflect an oversupply in vessels that will continue
to “pressure” freight rates, according to a statement by the
ratings company. MISC fell 1.1 percent to 7.20 ringgit.        Selangor Properties Bhd. (SPR)  : The property developer
had a profit of 30.2 million ringgit in the second quarter ended
April 30, compared with a loss of 25.6 million ringgit a year
earlier, it said in a statement. The stock fell 0.3 percent to
3.75 ringgit.        Teck Guan Perdana Bhd. (TGN)  : The Malaysian cocoa and
palm oil producer said profit in the first quarter ended April
30 rose 52 percent from a year earlier to 4.03 million ringgit,
according to a stock exchange filing. Teck Guan last traded at
70 sen on June 23.       V.S. Industry Bhd. (VSI MK): The electronics parts and
components manufacturer’s profit in the third quarter ended
April 30 rose 32 percent from a year earlier to 8.56 million
ringgit, according to a company statement. The stock added 0.6
percent to 1.66 ringgit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
